Hi everyone! Can the output of a custom code action in a workflow be used in any other way than using it in a ‘Copy property value’?
Currently the only other place is a “value equals branch” action, but we have plans to make the outputs available in more places in the future
value equals branch, is that a filter?
And sounds great! I currently need a setup where I know if I can proceed with the workflow based on data I fetch with custom code.
Yup, that sounds like a good use case for a “value equals branch.” It’s just a special type of if-then branch that only checks for whether the selected property or output exactly matches a value.
Awesome! That is a great solution

Hi Guys, Im tring to improve google speed insight, and I’m checking at the image options adding a custom maximum width in the module, but when I check the mobile google speed insight in mobile it is calling a bigger size for my image, what am i doing wrong?

Attaching my settings in HubSpot, and attaching the google speed image loading in mobile

Hey there, sorry to hear you’re having trouble logging in.

We have a help doc which shows troubleshooting steps you can take. If they don’t resolve the issue, you can use a form at the bottom of the page to contact support.
<https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/account/why-can-t-i-log-into-HubSpot?_ga=2.185710507.309380568.1629724853-1888876121.1626111823>

Let me know if you have trouble accessing this page.

Those options there are really only specifying the visual size on screen. They will inline some CSS and set the width and height attributes on the img element.

If you want to bring in the image at a certain size you will either need to compress it yourself or use the `resize_image_url` function
